---
import Base from "../layouts/lilybaseweb.astro";
---

<Base title="Terms of Service — Lily">
  <style>
    .policy-container {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 5rem auto;
      padding: 0 2rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    
    .policy-container h1 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--pink-mid);
    }

    .policy-meta {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    
    .policy-container h2 {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .policy-container p {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 300;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }
    
    .policy-container ul {
      margin-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    
    .policy-container li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="policy-container">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="policy-meta">Last Updated: June 16, 2026</p>

    <p>
      By inviting Lily to your Discord server or using our website, you agree to comply with and be bound by the following Terms of Service.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p>
      Please read these terms carefully. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you are prohibited from using the bot or accessing our website services.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Permitted Use</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to use Lily in compliance with all applicable laws and Discord's Developer Terms of Service. You may not:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the bot for malicious harassment, raid coordination, or distributing prohibited material.</li>
      <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, exploit, or disrupt the bot's API gateway and local database services.</li>
      <li>Abuse the simulator sandbox on this website to flood requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
    <p>
      Lily is provided "as is" and "as available". We make no warranties, express or implied, regarding the bot's uptime, reliability, or completeness of moderation logs. We are not responsible for user actions or moderation decisions made using our warning/banning tools.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      In no event shall the creators of Lily be liable for any damages (including, without limitation, loss of data, server disruption, or configuration mishaps) arising from the use or inability to use the bot.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Termination</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to suspend or block servers/users from using Lily if these terms are violated or if bot API usage patterns threaten backend performance.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
